        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXT_SUBSCRIPTION_RESTHOOK_DELIVER_LATEST_VERSION

        public static final String EXT_SUBSCRIPTION_RESTHOOK_DELIVER_LATEST_VERSION
        This extension URL indicates whether a REST HOOK delivery should reload the resource and deliver the latest version always. This could be useful for example if a resource which triggers a subscription gets updated many times in short succession and there is no value in delivering the older versions.

        Note that if the resource is now deleted, this may cause the delivery to be cancelled altogether.

        This extension should be of type boolean and should be placed on the Subscription.channel element.

        See Also:
